    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and Camshaft - Installation - Crankshaft and Timing
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26508.3.4" svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="5">
        <title>Crankshaft and Timing</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure the crankshaft has been inspected per instructions found within this section prior to
                    proceeding.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a lint-free cloth to wipe the crankcase bearing supports free of oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect each bearing. Replace all bearings that are scored, chipped, or worn.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When inserting main bearings in the crankcase, be sure that there is no oil between the back side
                    of the bearing and crankcase bearing saddles.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f3000947" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ03/J03017.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Install upper crankshaft main bearings (thrust bearing shown)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place upper main bearings in the crankcase. Make sure locking tabs on bearings are snapped
                in the crankcase saddle and oil holes in bearings line up with oil holes in crankcase.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Crankshaft thrust bearing is installed at the number 3 upper main bearing journal.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000948" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06048.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Lubricating the upper main bearings</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the upper main bearings with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000949" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj03/j03036.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Installing the Crankshaft Timing Tool</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align index marks on both camshaft gear and primary balancer gear so that they are adjacent
                to each other. Install Crankshaft Timing Tool through machined holes in both balancer gear and camshaft
                gear as well as the machined hole in crankcase. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_190.xml" xrefid="E30009C">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000950" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ03/J03016.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing crankshaft into crankcase</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolts threaded into crankshaft</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Lifting sling</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a bolt in each end of the crankshaft. Attach hoist and lifting sling around crankshaft
                bolts and carefully lower onto the four main bearings.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possible death, use an appropriately sized lifting sling and
                    hoist equipped with a safety latch on hook. See
                    <hotlnk xrefid="safety">"Safety Information</hotlnk>."
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f3000951" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ03/J03029.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crankshaft / camshaft / primary balancer timing alignment</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Flywheel alignment pin</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft gear (1 of 2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft gear timing mark</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Primary balancer gear timing mark</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Primary balancer gear</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft gear</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Timing tool thru hole</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install crankshaft so that index mark aligns with both camshaft and primary balancer index
                marks.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
